headline: Wall Street Lunch: 3rd Straight FOMC Cut, But Dissents Grow
summary: As widely expected, the Federal Open Market Committee reduced its benchmark interest rate by 25 basis points on Wednesday, its third straight cut.

headline: Applied Materials (AMAT): Assessing Valuation After a Strong 1-Year Share Price Rally
summary: Applied Materials (AMAT) has quietly added momentum, with the stock up around 14% over the past month and roughly 57% over the past year. This has prompted a closer look at what might be driving sentiment. See our latest analysis for Applied Materials.
